task_description:
Create a new Evolution API HTTP client service to replace the GREEN-API SDK.

## Create new file: src/evolution/evolution-api.client.ts

This service handles all HTTP communication with Evolution API. All requests need the header: apikey: {apiKey}

### Methods to implement:

1. constructor(baseUrl: string, apiKey: string)

2. sendText(instanceName: string, number: string, text: string)
   - POST {baseUrl}/message/sendText/{instanceName}
   - Body: { number, text }

3. sendMedia(instanceName: string, number: string, mediaUrl: string, caption?: string, mediaType?: string)
   - POST {baseUrl}/message/sendMedia/{instanceName}
   - Body: { number, mediatype, media, caption }

4. getConnectionState(instanceName: string)
   - GET {baseUrl}/instance/connectionState/{instanceName}
   - Returns: { state: 'open' | 'close' | 'connecting' }

5. setWebhook(instanceName: string, webhookUrl: string, events: string[])
   - POST {baseUrl}/webhook/set/{instanceName}
   - Body: { url: webhookUrl, events, webhook_by_events: true }

6. fetchInstances()
   - GET {baseUrl}/instance/fetchInstances
   - Returns list of all instances

## Also create: src/evolution/evolution.module.ts
- NestJS module that exports EvolutionApiClient as a provider

Use axios for HTTP calls (already in package.json).
Include proper error handling and logging using NestJS Logger.
